§<~>1<~>.<~>``<~>The<~>world<~>is<~>my<~>idea<~>:<~>''<~>--<~>this<~>is<~>a<~>truth<~>which<~>holds<~>good<~>for<~>*NL*<~>everything<~>that<~>lives<~>and<~>knows<~>,<~>though<~>man<~>alone<~>can<~>bring<~>it<~>into<~>*NL*<~>reflective<~>and<~>abstract<~>consciousness<~>.<~>If<~>he<~>really<~>does<~>this<~>,<~>he<~>has<~>*NL*<~>attained<~>to<~>philosophical<~>wisdom<~>.<~>It<~>then<~>becomes<~>clear<~>and<~>certain<~>to<~>him<~>*NL*<~>that<~>what<~>he<~>knows<~>is<~>not<~>a<~>sun<~>and<~>an<~>earth<~>,<~>but<~>only<~>an<~>eye<~>that<~>sees<~>a<~>*NL*<~>sun<~>,<~>a<~>hand<~>that<~>feels<~>an<~>earth<~>;<~>that<~>the<~>world<~>which<~>surrounds<~>him<~>is<~>*NL*<~>there<~>only<~>as<~>idea<~>,<~>i.e.<~>,<~>only<~>in<~>relation<~>to<~>something<~>else<~>,<~>the<~>*NL*<~>consciousness<~>,<~>which<~>is<~>himself<~>.<~>If<~>any<~>truth<~>can<~>be<~>asserted<~>a<~>priori<~>,<~>*NL*<~>it<~>is<~>this<~>:<~>for<~>it<~>is<~>the<~>expression<~>of<~>the<~>most<~>general<~>form<~>of<~>all<~>*NL*<~>possible<~>and<~>thinkable<~>experience<~>:<~>a<~>form<~>which<~>is<~>more<~>general<~>than<~>time<~>,<~>*NL*<~>or<~>space<~>,<~>or<~>causality<~>,<~>for<~>they<~>all<~>presuppose<~>it<~>;<~>and<~>each<~>of<~>these<~>,<~>*NL*<~>which<~>we<~>have<~>seen<~>to<~>be<~>just<~>so<~>many<~>modes<~>of<~>the<~>principle<~>of<~>sufficient<~>*NL*<~>reason<~>,<~>is<~>valid<~>only<~>for<~>a<~>particular<~>class<~>of<~>ideas<~>;<~>whereas<~>the<~>*NL*<~>antithesis<~>of<~>object<~>and<~>subject<~>is<~>the<~>common<~>form<~>of<~>all<~>these<~>classes<~>,<~>*NL*<~>is<~>that<~>form<~>under<~>which<~>alone<~>any<~>idea<~>of<~>whatever<~>kind<~>it<~>may<~>be<~>,<~>*NL*<~>abstract<~>or<~>intuitive<~>,<~>pure<~>or<~>empirical<~>,<~>is<~>possible<~>and<~>thinkable<~>.<~>No<~>*NL*<~>truth<~>therefore<~>is<~>more<~>certain<~>,<~>more<~>independent<~>of<~>all<~>others<~>,<~>and<~>less<~>*NL*<~>in<~>need<~>of<~>proof<~>than<~>this<~>,<~>that<~>all<~>that<~>exists<~>for<~>knowledge<~>,<~>and<~>*NL*<~>therefore<~>thi